"event_uuid":"80b230b4-73a0-4374-8911-8c624572999f","position":{"commit_sha":"c6ff53a33a4a7e483ce7c05565beb92de9f1fa05","position":"1784756158922505001-80b230b4-73a0-4374-8911-8c624572999f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"380c04e6296a305a345a6d9af83bc4a200d434ed53e55a0187799199c92ee68b","event_uuid":"40301cda-2e5e-43a1-aa67-4fcb957c801c","position":{"commit_sha":"66f0c8fe0094356f597b4c881e74e9e185ba39e2","position":"1784756480900237607-40301cda-2e5e-43a1-aa67-4fcb957c801c"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"b3ee85f1-444b-4969-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[],"created_at":1784695338012815001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"4e6fc0c0-76f8-48ce-8f2d-bd6d42bfde8d","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798"},{"link_uuid":"86e13481-97da-4d7f-a912-4b46cfc3a895","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"6eee-f98b-716c-48eb"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nWith the `Backend` interface defined (S2 [rebar:ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798]), the reconciler still has\nno way to *choose* a backend: the vendor is implicit in which module is imported. This story\nadds the **selection infrastructure only** — a `reconciler.backend` config key, an in-tree\nregistry, and a `select_backend()` entry point that returns the `Backend` for the configured\nkey. It deliberately does **not** rewire any existing consumer (the `_load_acli` seams, the\n`AcliClient` construction sites, or the differ/apply leaks) — that is S4\n[rebar:6673-7636-a116-4f90], which routes *all* consumers through the port at once. Keeping\nselection and rewiring in separate stories avoids the trap the first draft hit: `_load_acli()`\nreturns the acli **module** (callers do `acli_mod.AcliClient(...)`), so it cannot be quietly\n\"delegated to `select_backend`\" without changing its contract and the tests that patch it —\nthat contract change belongs with the coordinated rewire in S4.\n\n**Grounded config mechanism.** The reconciler is *not* configured by\n`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/config.py` (that module is flat domain constants —\n`EXCLUDED_FIELDS`, status-mapping dicts — with no settings namespace). Runtime settings come\nfrom the **app-level typed config**: `rebar.config.load_config()` returns a `Config` dataclass\nwith a first-class `[reconciler]` section (`ReconcilerConfig` at\n`src/rebar/_config_schema.py:475`, field `jira_cli_timeout` at `:476`), already consumed by the reconciler at\n`acli_subprocess.py:71` as `load_config().reconciler.jira_cli_timeout`. So the backend selector\nis a **new field on `ReconcilerConfig`**, read as `load_config().reconciler.backend` — mirroring\nthe existing `jira_cli_timeout` field exactly. `select_backend(config)` takes that app-level\n`Config` object.\n\nEdit-set:\n- `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` — add `backend: str = \"jira\"` to the `ReconcilerConfig`\n  dataclass (class def `:475`; add the field beside `jira_cli_timeout` at `:476`), and register a **constrained coercer** for it\n  in the `\"reconciler\"` coercer table (the `\"reconciler\": {...}` block opening at `:653`) using the\n  existing `_as_choice(v, k, {\"jira\"})` pattern (`:117`) — the same mechanism `sync.push`/`pull`\n  (`:609`–`:610`) and `mcp.transport` (`:617`) use. This gives **config-load static validation**\n  (an unknown key raises `ConfigError` naming the allowed choices) and a free\n  `REBAR_RECONCILER_BACKEND` env override (auto-derived by the env layer, `_config_sources.py`).\n  The static choice-set (`{\"jira\"}` today) is the config-load guard; the *registry* below does\n  the authoritative runtime object lookup. A second backend adds its key to **both** the\n  `_as_choice` set and the registry.\n- New `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend_registry.py` — a `register(key, factory)`\n  decorator, a `select_backend(config)` resolver (takes the app-level `Config`, reads\n  `config.reconciler.backend`), and a **test-only reset** helper\n  (`_reset_registry_for_test()` context manager), since the registry is process-lifetime module\n  state.\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py` — decorate `JiraBackend` with\n  `@register(\"jira\", …)` (the `JiraBackend` class itself is introduced by S2, a prerequisite;\n  this story only adds its registration).\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/__init__.py` — **currently comment-only (zero\n  imports)**; add `from .jira import backend as _jira_backend  # noqa: F401` so importing the\n  `adapters` package fires each shipped adapter's `@register` side-effect. This is the import\n  trigger the registry depends on (the earlier draft wrongly said this file already imports each\n  adapter — it does not).\n\n*No `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/config.py` change and no new\n`rebar_reconciler/_config_schema.py`* — the earlier draft named both in error; the real config\nhome is the app-level `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` above.\n\n## Approach\n\nThe registry is a module-level dict populated by an idempotent `register` decorator (the\nin-tree decorator-registry style rebar uses elsewhere — no setuptools entry-points; a second\nbackend is added in-tree under `adapters/<x>/`). `select_backend(config)` reads\n`config.reconciler.backend` off the passed app-level `Config`, looks up the factory, and\nconstructs the `Backend`; an unknown key (one that somehow bypassed the `_as_choice` load-time\nguard) raises a registry error naming the registered keys. Registration happens as a\nside-effect of importing `adapters/jira/backend.py`. To make that deterministic regardless of\ncaller import order, `select_backend` **lazily imports `rebar_reconciler.adapters` inside the\nfunction** (before resolving the key), and `adapters/__init__.py` is edited to\n`from .jira import backend` — so the first `select_backend` call is guaranteed to populate the\nregistry. The lazy in-function import also avoids a circular import\n(`adapters/jira/backend.py` imports the registry to use `@register`, so the registry module must\nnot import the adapters at *its* module top). The reset helper lets the teeth test\nregister a `FakeBackend` and tear it down without leaking process state. **No consumer is\nrewired here** — `select_backend` is proven equivalent to today's construction in isolation;\nS4 changes the call sites.\n\n## Scope\n\n- The `reconciler.backend` field on `ReconcilerConfig` + its `_as_choice` coercer (static-key\n  validation) + default `\"jira\"`, in `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`.\n- The registry module (`register` + `select_backend` + `_reset_registry_for_test`) and\n  `JiraBackend`'s registration.\n- **Out of scope:** rewiring `_load_acli` / the `AcliClient` construction sites / the\n  differ/apply leaks (all S4); physically relocating vendor modules (S5\n  [rebar:dfb9-d2d1-455d-48d9]); the `Backend`/`JiraBackend` interface itself (S2, prerequisite);\n  a doc note in ADR 0035 that selection is config-driven (a one-line S1/ADR follow-up, tracked\n  there, not blocking here).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Tier:** unit, RED-first (each test authored and seen failing for the right reason before\n  the code exists).\n- **Config-schema unit** (app-level typed config — `pytest tests/unit/test_config_typed.py`\n  plus a new focused `tests/unit/test_config_reconciler_backend.py`; NOT the engine-side\n  `rebar_reconciler/state/test_config.py`, which covers the flat domain constants):\n  `load_config()` on a default config yields\n  `reconciler.backend == \"jira\"`; a `rebar.toml` with `[tool.rebar.reconciler] backend = \"nope\"`\n  is rejected at **config-load** by the `_as_choice` coercer with a `ConfigError` naming the\n  allowed keys (independent of the registry); `REBAR_RECONCILER_BACKEND=jira` env override\n  resolves.\n- **Registry unit** (`pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_registry.py`, a new\n  file): `select_backend(load_config())` returns a `JiraBackend` for the default; `register` is\n  idempotent (same key+factory = no-op; a conflicting factory for the same key raises);\n  `_reset_registry_for_test` round-trips (state after exit == state before enter).\n- **Equivalence:** `select_backend(load_config())` returns a `Backend` whose `TicketTransport`\n  is an `AcliClient` constructed from the **same** `resolve_jira_settings()` values as today's\n  direct construction (asserted against the resolved `JiraSettings` fields\n  url/user/api_token — not a live Jira call).\n- **Teeth:** via `_reset_registry_for_test`, register a `FakeBackend` under a test key, point a\n  `Config` at it (`reconciler.backend` set to that key with the choice-set temporarily widened\n  in the test), and assert `select_backend` returns the fake — then confirm reverting the\n  registration makes the same lookup raise. Confirms selection is honored, not hard-coded.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `ReconcilerConfig.backend` exists in `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, defaults to `\"jira\"`,\n  and a value outside the `_as_choice` set is rejected at config-load with a `ConfigError`\n  naming the allowed keys — verified by\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_config_typed.py tests/unit/test_config_reconciler_backend.py`\n  (valid default resolves + unknown value raises), exit 0.\n- [ ] `select_backend(config)` accepts the app-level `Config` (`rebar.config.load_config()`\n  return type), reads `config.reconciler.backend`, and returns a `Backend`; the default returns\n  a `JiraBackend` whose transport is an `AcliClient` built from the same `resolve_jira_settings()`\n  values as today — verified by `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_registry.py -k equivalence`, exit 0.\n- [ ] `register` is idempotent (same key+factory = no-op; conflicting factory raises) and\n  `_reset_registry_for_test` round-trips registry state — verified by\n  `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_registry.py -k \"idempotent or reset\"`, exit 0.\n- [ ] **Teeth:** with `_reset_registry_for_test`, a `FakeBackend` registered under a test key and\n  a `Config` pointed at it makes `select_backend` return that fake (selection is honored, not\n  hard-coded to Jira), and reverting the registration makes the same lookup raise — verified by\n  `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_registry.py -k \"teeth or fake or dispatch\"`,\n  exit 0.\n- [ ] No existing consumer (`_load_acli`, the `AcliClient` construction sites, the differ/apply\n  modules) is modified — verified by `git diff --name-only origin/main` listing only\n  `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend_registry.py`,\n  `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/__init__.py`,\n  `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py`, and files under `tests/`\n  (no other `src/` path present — in particular no `_load_acli`/differ/apply module).\n- [ ] Every `src/rebar/**/*.py` stays within the 800-LOC cap — verified by\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py`, exit 0.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_config_schema.py","reason":"Add backend field to ReconcilerConfig + _as_choice coercer in the reconciler coercer table (static-key load-time validation)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend_registry.py","reason":"New in-tree register() decorator + select_backend(config) + _reset_registry_for_test"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/__init__.py","reason":"Lazy-import .jira.backend so JiraBackend registration happens as an import side-effect"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py","reason":"Register JiraBackend under key jira via @register decorator"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798"],["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"],["relates_to","6eee-f98b-716c-48eb"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"2d9c959c-3951-40a7-9721-b3f43c685a47","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["reconciler","vendor-adapter","registry"],"ticket_id":"94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75","ticket_type":"story","title":"Backend selection infrastructure: reconciler.backend config + in-tree registry + select_backend() + JiraBackend registration (no consumer rewiring)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["6e0c3618-966b-4a84-a621-daa84c59692a","96e83901-9574-44af-b43d-434df41797a6","0f19655c-7460-4346-916c-bcc5f943ce78","4e6fc0c0-76f8-48ce-8f2d-bd6d42bfde8d","f683af77-333d-4e03-9f3f-edbe77de26fc","dff00daa-4fa0-473c-8e38-ae8742c34f89","32ad156b-5dbb-4892-b411-debe5aebd704","f464fb86-4811-4382-8457-fb795b5f8bdf","b60bdfe7-ccf1-4868-bafe-4a2bc9a314ec","86e13481-97da-4d7f-a912-4b46cfc3a895","084d52cb-dc47-472f-a27e-9f8276bc12e1","027a4751-aec2-4894-9a72-583c19f9de02","eee5179f-3978-4ac1-b375-0f05a14ba4ea","8e5e1019-c17f-4633-b95b-cbfb1b7c8154","387d8e96-148e-47b6-8f0f-963d83614346","860d499e-20f9-42e3-bdb9-5d0afe496ac5","2e177b12-367d-4b79-b8a7-67b1769d671d","a93e521b-7b30-4193-b8ef-1039a0accee4","09a4689c-e36d-44b9-a7c6-b4bc1a02a85d","5506537c-1165-44bc-bee9-e2ec8471a1ed","2d9c959c-3951-40a7-9721-b3f43c685a47","80b230b4-73a0-4374-8911-8c624572999f","40301cda-2e5e-43a1-aa67-4fcb957c801c"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784756480900237608,"uuid":"719207e3-823b-4361-b24e-30f303eaf02f"}